---
title: Sweet Apple Pork Chops with Mashed Potatoes and Snap Peas
description: Pork has a way of embracing fruity flavors like no other protein. In this recipe, we’re smothering it in chunks of tender, saucy apple, which add a welcome touch of sweetness to the mildness of the meat. On the side, we’ve got sugar snap peas and a mash that tucks cauliflower into the potatoes—it’s so good, no one will notice that you snuck in some extra veggies!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sweet-apple-pork-tenderloin-695038c0.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sweet-apple-pork-tenderloin-5c50a62be3f33902b31ed712-dd04ef4b.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-apple-pork-tenderloin-5c50a62be3f33902b31ed712
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 370 mg
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch cubes. (TIP: For a smoother mash, peel potatoes first.) Place in a large #pot with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain and return to pot. Keep covered until ready to mash.

While potatoes cook, trim any tough ends or strings from @Sugar Snap Peas{6%ounce}. Toss on a #baking sheet with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @Pork Chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Dried Thyme{1/2%tsp} (we sent more). Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate. Wipe out pan.

Halve, core, and dice @Apple{1} into ½-inch pieces. Heat @Butter{1%tablespoon} and a drizzle of oil in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add apple; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{5-7%minutes}. Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and ½ cup water. Increase heat to medium high and cook until apple is tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Add @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} and @Butter{1%tablespoon} to #pot with potatoes. (TIP: If potatoes have cooled, reheat briefly over low heat.) Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork until mostly smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide snap peas, potatoes, and pork between plates. Top pork with sauce, making sure to include apple pieces.